{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/spawnCheck(waitStatus:)"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"waitStatus"},{"text":" indicates the child exited abnormally","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(e.g. with a nonzero exit code, or via a fatal signal).","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"spawnCheck","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"waitStatus","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_sync()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_child_watch_add()"},{"type":"text","text":" family of APIs return the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"status of subprocesses encoded in a platform-specific way."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"On Unix, this is guaranteed to be in the same format "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"waitpid()"},{"text":" returns,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and on Windows it is guaranteed to be the result of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GetExitCodeProcess()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to the introduction of this function in GLib 2.34, interpreting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"waitStatus","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" required use of platform-specific APIs, which is problematic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for software using GLib as a cross-platform layer.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, many programs simply want to determine whether or not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the child exited successfully, and either propagate a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/GLibError"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"print a message to standard error. In that common case, this function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be used. Note that the error message in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" will contain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"human-readable information about the wait status.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"domain","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"code","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" have special semantics in the case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"where the process has an “exit code”, as opposed to being killed by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a signal. On Unix, this happens if "},{"code":"WIFEXITED()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" would be true of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"waitStatus"},{"type":"text","text":". On Windows, it is always the case."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The special semantics are that the actual exit code will be the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"code set in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":", and the domain will be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_SPAWN_EXIT_ERROR"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This allows you to differentiate between different exit codes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the process was terminated by some means other than an exit","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"status (for example if it was killed by a signal), the domain will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"G_SPAWN_ERROR","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and the code will be ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"failed"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function just offers convenience; you can of course also check"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the available platform via a macro such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OS_UNIX"},{"type":"text","text":", and use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WIFEXITED()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WEXITSTATUS()"},{"text":" on ","type":"text"},{"code":"waitStatus","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. Do not attempt"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to scan or parse the error message string; it may be translated and\/or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"change in future versions of GLib.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to version 2.70, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_check_exit_status()"},{"type":"text","text":" provides the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functionality, although under a misleading name.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/spawncheck(waitstatus:)"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function","externalID":"s:4GLib10spawnCheck10waitStatusSbSi_tKF","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":